name: THE SNOWBIRDS Visit Calgary! Nine Canadair CT-114 Tutors at YYC [4K]
description:
Last week, the Canadian Forces Snowbirds transited through Calgary en route from Moose Jaw to a show in Kelowna.

It's always a pleasure to see them here, especially among the usual airliner traffic at YYC! Enjoy the video!

FLIGHT INFORMATION

Aircraft: Canadair CT-114 Tutor (x9)
Livery: Standard
Engines: 1x Orenda J85-CAN-40
Registration: Many
Route: Moose Jaw (YMJ) - Calgary (YYC) - Kelowna (YLW)
Callsign: Snowbird 10 / Snowbird 1 Flight, etc.
